Can’t rate as I am doing my DD. Here are some questions, thoughts and my $02:
1) You should disclose the cap rates you are buying the properties at?
2) You should disclose the loan terms of each property leveraged?
3) If properties are purchased with all cash then financed, how do we (investors) follow the loan disbursements? Should be rolled back into the fund and reinvested. Am sure this is happening but transparency is critical for new/less-known/non-public entities.
4) You should disclose to investors on-going cash flow analyses on each property held.
5) I see more petro, secondary market locations and non-credit tenants in the track-record portfolio than I am initially comfortable with. Seems like more DD on your purchase advisors’ part could produce less risk as quality NNN properties are out there…you just have to work harder to find them. Understand the need to get money out and working but at what cost risk-wise?
